The paper proposes a new architecture for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and evaluates it on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the advantages of the proposed approach, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as gradient updates, which could make it relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
